      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Absolutely, your eye condition sounds like a classic case of dry eye syndrome, likely exacerbated by prolonged screen time. The best course of action is to use lubricating eye drops, but make sure to use a preservative-free formula to avoid irritation. Try to apply them every two hours while you're working, and don't forget to blink more often to help distribute tears evenly across your eyes. If the discomfort persists, consider taking a break from the screen every hour to rest your eyes.",
