      "content": "You can absolutely use the lubricating eye drops and ibuprofen together. The eye drops will soothe your eyes, while the ibuprofen will help with the pain and inflammation. Just make sure to follow the recommended dosage for ibuprofen, and be aware that it's a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID), so it can have some side effects if taken too frequently or in high doses. But if you're feeling this level of discomfort, it's perfectly fine to take both to get relief. Just remember, if your eye condition doesn't improve or worsens, you should consult a healthcare professional.",
